    # Split data using pertinent columns and creating training and testing data
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
X = df[['Avg. Session Length', 'Time on App', 'Time on Website', 'Length of Membership']]
y = df['Yearly Amount Spent']

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=.3, random_state=13)
    # Split data using pertinent columns and creating training and testing data from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split X = df[['Avg. Session Length', 'Time on App', 'Time on Website', 'Length of Membership']] y = df['Yearly Amount Spent'] X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=.3, random_state=13)

    # Create Linear Regression Instance
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
lm = LinearRegression()

# Fit model using training data
lm.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Create predictions from model
predictions = lm.predict(X_test)
    # Create Linear Regression Instance from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression lm = LinearRegression() # Fit model using training data lm.fit(X_train, y_train) # Create predictions from model predictions = lm.predict(X_test)

    InÂ [117]:

    # Get some metrics
from sklearn import metrics
print(f'MAE: {metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test,predictions)}')
print(f'MSE: {metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,predictions)}')
print(f'RMSE: {(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,predictions))**(1/2)}')
print(f'R^2: {metrics.explained_variance_score(y_test,predictions)}')
    # Get some metrics from sklearn import metrics print(f'MAE: {metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test,predictions)}') print(f'MSE: {metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,predictions)}') print(f'RMSE: {(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,predictions))**(1/2)}') print(f'R^2: {metrics.explained_variance_score(y_test,predictions)}')
